<div class="container" style="margin-top: 20px;">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col border">
            <h3>Progression</h3>
            <table id="leveltable" style="width: 100%;">
                <tr>
                    <th>Progression</th>
                    <th>B Locker</th>
                    <th>Troff N Scoff</th>
                </tr>
                {% for i in range(0, 8) %}
                    <tr>
                        <td>Level {{ i + 1 }}</td>
                        <td>
                            <input class="form-control"
                                   min="0"
                                   max="200"
                                   name="blocker_{{ i }}"
                                   id="blocker_{{ i }}"
                                   style="width: 100%;"
                                   value="{{ i+1 }}"
                                   type="number"
                                   title="You can adjust each individual B Locker amount to any number between 0-200. &#013;Note that you could make it impossible to beat the game glitchless if certain levels are set too high, as the program does not validate if a game is beatable glitchless with adjusted B Locker settings. &#013;If you are unsure what to adjust the level values to, use the presets dropdown instead."/>
                        </td>
                        {% if i < 7 %}
                            <td>
                                <input class="form-control"
                                       min="0"
                                       max="500"
                                       name="troff_{{ i }}"
                                       id="troff_{{ i }}"
                                       style="width: 100%;"
                                       value="{{ i+1 }}"
                                       type="number"
                                       title="You can adjust each individual Troff n Scoff amount to any number between 1-500. &#013;Note that you could make it impossible to beat the game glitchless if early levels are set too high, as the program does not validate if a game is beatable glitchless with adjusted Troff n Scoff settings. &#013;If you are unsure what to adjust the level values to, use the presets dropdown instead."/>
                            </td>
                        {% endif %}
                    </tr>
                {% endfor %}
            </table>
            <div class="form-check form-switch w-75">
                <label title="Randomize Required B-Locker totals">
                    <input class="form-check-input"
                           type="checkbox"
                           name="randomize_blocker_required_amounts"
                           id="randomize_blocker_required_amounts"
                           value="True"/>
                    Random B-Lockers
                </label>
            </div>
            <div class="form-check form-switch w-75">
                <label title="Randomize Required CB totals">
                    <input class="form-check-input"
                           type="checkbox"
                           name="randomize_cb_required_amounts"
                           id="randomize_cb_required_amounts"
                           value="True"/>
                    Random Troff Bananas
                </label>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col border">
            <h3>Damage Options</h3>
            <div>
                Damage
                <select name="damage_amount"
                        style="width: 60%;"
                        class="form-select center-div"
                        aria-label="Damage Options">
                    <option selected value="default">
                        Normal
                    </option>
                    <option value="ohko">
                        OHKO
                    </option>
                    <option value="double">
                        Double Damage
                    </option>
                    <option value="quad">
                        Quad Damage
                    </option>
                </select>
            </div>
            <table class="table table-striped table-dark">
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <div class="form-check form-switch w-75">
                            <label title="Tag Barrels, Boss Fights, Candy Upgrades etc don't heal you like they normally would.">
                                <input class="form-check-input"
                                       type="checkbox"
                                       name="no_healing"
                                       value="False"/>
                                No Heals
                            </label>
                        </div>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <div class="form-check form-switch w-75">
                            <label title="No melons are dropped from enemies." style="text-align: left;">
                                <input class="form-check-input"
                                       type="checkbox"
                                       name="no_melons"
                                       value="False"/>
                                No Melon Slice Drops
                            </label>
                        </div>
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>
                        <div class="form-check form-switch w-75">
                            <label title="Enabling this setting means logic may expect you to do some difficult shooting challenges without help. If this setting is disabled, then the following requirements exist: &#013; * Lanky's attic in Fungi Forest requires homing ammo. &#013; * Donkey's 5 door cabin in Crystal Caves requires homing ammo. &#013; * Tiny's trash can in Creepy Castle requires homing ammo &#013; * Chunky's tree banana in Creepy Castle requires sniper scope. (This requirement can be skipped by shooting from below the switch.) &#013; * Chunky's shooting barrel in Hideout Helm requires either sniper scope or homing ammo."
                                   style="text-align: left;">
                                <input class="form-check-input"
                                       type="checkbox"
                                       name="hard_shooting"
                                       value="False"/>
                                Hard Shooting
                            </label>
                        </div>
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
